
[Initial pose estimate] (Using roslaunch):

Subscribing /odom data for initial pose positions

1. Open terminal and type:

$ roslaunch turtlebot3_gazebo turtlebot3_world.launch

2. Open new terminal and type:

$ roslaunch autonomous initial_pose2.launch map_file:=$HOME/TB3_WORLD.yaml

*Ensure you still have the map that you have saved previously in the HOME directory
*This launch file involves the following node: initial_pose2.py

*ensure that your python codes are in the src folder of your autonomous package
*ensure you have given permissions to your python files (1. cd to directory; 2. chmod +x initial_pose2.py)

3. Observe in the RViz application that the TB3â€™s pose estimate will be automatically executed
